$ VBA functions: varType

`varType` returns a number that indicates the → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes[datatype] of a → development/languages/VBA/language/variables.
-
The returned number corresponds to one of the `vb…` constants that are defined by VBA.

An array is special in that it adds the type number of the elements in the array to `vbArray` (8192).


gh|about-VBA|/functions/varType.bas||

VBA defines a few constants for these numbers, such as `vbInteger`, `vbLong`, `vbDate`, `vbEmpty`, `vbNull` etc.

There is also a variable type *error* whose corresponding value is 10 and constant is `vbError`.

Compare with the → development/languages/VBA/functions/typeName[`typeName`] function.

sa:
  → development/languages/VBA/functions[VBA functions]
